set.html: You've found the tools you've lost, right? Very well.
You will try to remove this orb again in minutes...
Meanwhile I've a favour to ask you.
I can't remember where I've left...
Can you go there, have a look around...
No problem! We'll be back soon!
Is this place more strange than others?
Well. The walls. They looks like the blob cave one...
Oh. That's right. It's like they...
Are we going to look for that papers for real?
Why not? Aren't you curious about this place?
Ah ah ah! I know you too much. You love adventures.
Well. Let's have a look around.
Yes. We are two Blamage and a young Whimage.
Obviously yes. The goblin guards checked it before.
Not at all! Well... where is that orb?
We've met a human in front of the village...
And now we've met a blob.
What's their plan? Humans and blobs have...
Probably we've to look around some more.
Y... yes. We're looking for some papers.
I. Found. One. Right. Side. From. Here.
Why they're trying to remove the blue orbs?
Everybody knows that they are symbols of God.
Tsk. You call them rebels now.
...is being rebel. I know you don't agree...
Enough talk. I'm here. With you.
That should mean something. Don't you think?
They fought each other for long time.
Mostly for empty reasons. Mostly for keeping peace.
War for peace is a nonsense.
That's why we formed the council.
Blamage, we've to find the rest.
Keep calm. I know what you're thinking.
Hi! We're here for removing the...
It looks like you've lost some strategy...
We've to understand what is this place.
It looks like we've a problem.
Probably. Let keep going with caution.
One for each clan. One for all.
The council was found by enlightened and driven by them.
Peace and equity for all. War and suffering for no one.
It looks like this place is where...
Very likely. This place looks like Roundlake Mountain...
...and I've seen some palms from the seaside.
I wonder who took part to the council.
I'm curious too. Let's keep going.
Let us go. We've to meet the council.
But I think you will never let us pass.
That's obvious. I'm not going to attack.
If you kill us I think that...
...you'll be promoted as member of council.
How you can be so sure about this?
But you have to trust me.
I think I'm starting to understand this council a bit...
You'll see. Let's keep looking for these...
Well. It looks like we've found the council.
The leader from our village is missing...
Please... we've to listen to them.
You have to stop your journey immediately.
Stupid fools! Do you think you're saving the world?
It's quite realistic. This guy here... he is...
...the hero sent by Gods. According to the...
We're not so sure that your mission...
...will solve anything. There is no menace to fight now.
Do you have seen any evil lord around?
We're gathering forces in order to fight our real enemy...
Please, can you listen to me first? I've a question.
Have you been elected in some way?
Nobody at our village knows anything about this council.
And the reason is really straightforward...
...on that sheet of paper. Can I read that?
It looks like there isn't any other way...
Time to peek that little scrap of paper.
I'm sure we'll found something interesting.
Ah ah ah! I knew it!
We are all free. But we are all different.
Someone can explain. Someone can understand.
Council mission is hard to understand.
Council mission is hard to explain.
We will build this core. We will join everything.
How they're going to do that?
As I suspected. They're going to conquer...
...everything in the name of the council. And then...
Whimage. Think about it a little more...
Gods or not Gods, gold is gold!
Tell me what is the word of Gods.
Do your really not know the word of Gods?
It's funny. Because it tells your story.
The word of Gods is also called...
...The Hero's Journey. It's a vague story in 9 steps.
1. The hero will be introducted to this world.
... I... woke up in a forest...
2. The hero will be called to action.
The blue orbs... told me what to do...
3. The hero will cross its threshold.
I've crossed the blob village and...
4. The hero will meet its mentor.
Right. Blamage. I saved you by goblins.
5. The hero will face its first challenge.
6. The hero will fall in temptation.
Whimage tried to stop us... And...
7. The hero will lose its mentor.
That's why I tried to stop you...
Now the thing gets interesting... because...
8. The hero will face its final battle.
We're going to our final battle but...
You're trying to change the word of God!
9. The hero will go back home.
Some versions of the Hero's Journey...
That's... right. So now I understand.
For sure. But I've seen some chests behind this place.
Danger. And chests. That means just one thing.
It's up to us to decide if we've to go there...
...or keep going ahead. Aren't you curious, hero?
So, you managed to arrive here.
And... the Blamage is still alive...
Word. Of. God. Not. True. Anymore.
We already won! We don't have to fight!
So. Your plan to conquer everything...
Have no use anymore. You're going...
...to go back to your villages, right?
We can't live in our villages anymore.
We. Too. Weak. To. Fight. No. Slaves.
...that is possible to live without stealing.
The Roundlake Mountain is getting too small...
So you're going to solve problems...
...despite their lives aren't bad, they have to...
Blobs. Peaceful. But. Weak. Don't. Train.
Losing. Battles. Against. Rogues. Steal. Food.
But that's not what God wants!
...just because they can't understand their condition?
That's terribly wrong. A God can't allow that.
That's why I was sent here.
To protect them, despite their conditions!
Is that the true mission of the hero?
So, you aren't going to stop here?
Very well. We'll try to change God's word...
It doesn't happen everyday! Ah ah ah!
8. The hero will face its final battle.
But... he battled with his mentor alive...
We know that our father have been here.
Look. Some rocks over there disappeared.
There is some kind of gate.
The more interesting things we find.
It's our turn to do what we want...
And we want to go through that gate.
There isn't anything more we can do.
This seems the end of our journey.
9. The hero will go back home.
We are going to go with you.
We think that our father is now...
...where you came from. We want to meet him.
There are a lot of things we want to ask to him.
I don't think we will come here again soon so...
Okay. Probably I must visit a blue orb again.
